<paragraph blockId="13.[151,756,1817,2098]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1817,1841]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">Comments.</emphasis>
Adetailed description of the external scent efferent system, an update of the terminology of male genitalia, photographs of 
<typeStatus box="[444,546,1882,1906]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">paratypes</typeStatus>
and of terminalia and genitalia for both sexes, and a distribution map for 
<emphasis box="[151,170,1946,1969]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[184,319,1946,1970]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">meridionalis</emphasis>
are provided.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,756,1817,2098]" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">
In addition to this species, 
<emphasis box="[476,495,1978,2001]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[509,596,1978,2002]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">ditarsus</emphasis>
is also known, not examined here for lack of material. 
<emphasis box="[589,608,2010,2033]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[624,711,2010,2034]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="334">ditarsus</emphasis>
